Retail Product Recommendation Engine

Overview : 

The Retail Product Recommendation Engine is a machine learning-based recommendation system developed to suggest fashion products based on product characteristics and user preferences. The project uses content-based filtering techniques to identify products that are similar in terms of category, brand, color, and size.

The system leverages TF-IDF vectorization and cosine similarity to compute product similarity scores and generate personalized recommendations. Product ratings are incorporated to prioritize highly rated items among the recommended results.

Objectives : 

* Build an intelligent recommendation system for fashion retail products.
* Analyze retail product data using exploratory data analysis (EDA).
* Generate relevant product recommendations using machine learning techniques.
* Improve customer experience by helping users discover similar products.
* Visualize retail insights through interactive dashboards.

Features : 

* Data preprocessing and cleaning
* Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
* Content-based recommendation system
* TF-IDF feature extraction
* Cosine similarity-based recommendations
* Rating-based recommendation ranking
* Interactive Streamlit web application
* Tableau dashboard for business insights

Technologies Used : 

* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Scikit-learn
* TF-IDF Vectorizer
* Cosine Similarity
* Streamlit
* Tableau

Dataset Attributes

The dataset contains retail product information including:

* User ID
* Product ID
* Product Name
* Brand
* Category
* Price
* Rating
* Color
* Size

Methodology

1. Data cleaning and preprocessing
2. Feature engineering using product attributes
3. TF-IDF vectorization of product features
4. Similarity calculation using cosine similarity
5. Recommendation generation based on product similarity
6. Ranking recommendations using product ratings
7. Visualization and deployment through Streamlit

Future Enhancements

* User-based collaborative filtering
* Hybrid recommendation system
* Real-time recommendation updates
* Deep learning-based recommendation models
* Integration with e-commerce platforms

Outcome

The project successfully demonstrates how machine learning can be used to recommend relevant fashion products, improve product discovery, and enhance customer shopping experiences through personalized recommendations.
